tourBios.exmtStatus: Finished T5 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Played in 20 Web.com Tour events, making nine cuts. Posted three top 25s, two of which were top 10s...Best finish of the year came in his second start at the Colombia Championship in Bogota, after making the cut on the number. Fired rounds of 65-66 on the weekend to grab a T8, his first top 10 in 24 Tour starts. The 131 total equaled the low 36 over the final two rounds (shared with winner Patrick Rodgers and Andrew Yun)...His other top 10 came in July at the Nova Scotia Open in Canada. Fired 68-68 on the weekend for a T10...Season ended on a disappointing note with four missed cuts in a row.

2014: Finished T21 at Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December. Was T68 after the fourth round. Shot 66-69 in the fifth and sixth rounds to significantly enhance his 2015 status...Played both PGA TOUR Latinoamérica and Mackenzie Tour - PGA TOUR Canada...Made nine appearances and four cuts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica. Best finish came in his last start, a T5 at the Mexico Open in October...On Mackenzie Tour played in 12 events and had one of golf's highlight rounds, a 59 at the ATB Financial Classic in August in Calgary. It was the first 59 in a Mackenzie Tour event. Holed out for eagle from 122 yards on the 18th hole to reach the magic number. The bogey-free score of 13-under par also included 11 birdies. T4, with rounds of 67-69 on the weekend after an opening-round 71. Jason Bohn has the only other sub-60 in the history of Mackenzie Tour, a 58 at the 2001 Bayer Championship in Sarnia, Ontario...His other top-10s came a month earlier, a sixth at the SIGA Dakota Dunes Open..In late-July, added a T5 at the Great Waterway Classic. Had eight top-25s in all, with just one missed cut. Finished the year 16th on the Order of Merit.



2013: After finishing runner-up at Mackenzie Tour Q-School, went on to make the cut in all nine of his starts, with six top-25s, including a T5, T6 and T7. Performance led to a 19th place spot on the final. 

2010: Was a member of the Web.com Tour. Made 19 starts, playing the weekend six times. Missed his first five cuts, then recorded his best performance, a T17, at the Mexico Open in June. Finished the season 134th on the money list.

 2009: Nine starts on Mackenzie Tour resulted in five cuts made and two top-25s, both of which came in his last two starts in the fall, a T20 and a T15. Was 109th on the final...Topped the money chart on the Gateway Tour Spring Series, making the cut in 13 of 16 starts, with nine top-25 finishes. 

2008: Played on the Dakota Tour, where he won four times and was the leading money-winner. 



2007: Made one PGA TOUR cut, which came in his first appearance, a T57 at the John Deere Classic...Played on the 2008 Dakota Tour, where he won four times and was the leading money-winner.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was an All-Big 12 selection and three-time Academic All-Big 12 at Nebraska...Won the 2003 Western Junior tournament and the 2006 North and South Amateur in Pinehurst, N.C.
tourBios.personal: Attended Millard (Nebraska) West High School and was named all-state in golf...Has used Mike Bender and his father, Curt, as his instructors...Favorite course played is Southern Hills CC in Tulsa, Oklahoma, and would like to play Augusta National GC...Never travels without his iPod...His first car was an Acura Legend and he now drives a Honda Accord...Favorite college team is the Nebraska Cornhuskers and is a big fan of the Minnesota Vikings...Favorite movie is "Tommy Boy," and his favorite book is Angels and Demons...Other favorites include steak and potatoes...Lists Tiger Woods, Zach Johnson and his father as the three who would round out his dream foursome...Puts skydiving and traveling the world on his bucket list.
